    "body": "\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n> builders are free to pay validators in whatever way they wish\r\n> \r\n> there is a soft norm amongst the community so far to use the **last** transaction of a block as a payment transaction from the builder to the proposer\r\n> \r\n> I don't think this is formally spec'd anywhere yet\r\n\r\nthanks , I am very interested in thisï¼ŒIs there a detailed documentation on this soft norm for newer to refer? The points I care about are: \r\n1. How to ensure that the block given by the builder will be paid to the validator after being proposed? \r\n2. How to ensure that the validator will propose the builder's block after obtaining the builder's amount? \r\n3. What is the role of relay? What happens without relay?\r\n4. How does pbs solve the problem of centralization?",
