    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "> How to ensure that the block given by the builder will be paid to the validator after being proposed?\r\n\r\nright now, validators trust builders/relays that they pay the amount they claim; there is research into payment proofs to remove this trust assumption\r\n\r\n> How to ensure that the validator will propose the builder's block after obtaining the builder's amount?\r\n\r\nin the current construction the validator cannot get the builder's payment until they have committed to the builder's block and moreover builders/relays have enough information once they get a validator's acceptance of a bid to publish the full block themselves\r\n\r\nrefer to the builder-specs: https://github.com/ethereum/builder-specs for more info\r\n\r\n> What is the role of relay? What happens without relay?\r\n\r\nrelays are a necessary, trusted component of the current design to facilitate interaction b/t mutually untrusting builders and proposers -- if a given validator trusts a given builder to not abuse them in any way then that validator can peer directly with the builder\r\n\r\n> How does pbs solve the problem of centralization?\r\n\r\nPBS aims to address validator centralization by removing any additional requirement for validators to also specialize in building valuable blocks so that validators can remain competitive amongst other validators with no additional effort",
